### Account Suggestion Logic
```go
// GetNextAccount suggests an account to rotate to
// Simple logic: return accounts in config order, user picks
func (c *RotationConfig) GetAccountsForProvider(provider string) []RotationAccount {
    var accounts []RotationAccount
    for _, acc := range c.Accounts {
        if acc.Provider == provider {
            accounts = append(accounts, acc)
        }
    }
    return accounts
}

// SuggestNextAccount returns the next account (simple: just return first non-current)
func (c *RotationConfig) SuggestNextAccount(provider, currentEmail string) *RotationAccount {
    for _, acc := range c.Accounts {
        if acc.Provider == provider && acc.Email != currentEmail {
            return &acc
        }
    }
    return nil
}
```

### Integration with rotate command
```go
// In rotate.go
func getTargetAccount(provider, currentEmail string) string {
    if rotateAccount != "" {
        return rotateAccount // User specified --account flag
    }

    accounts := cfg.Rotation.GetAccountsForProvider(provider)
    if len(accounts) == 0 {
        // No accounts configured, just prompt generically
        return "<your other Google account>"
    }

    // Suggest next account (skip current if known)
    suggested := cfg.Rotation.SuggestNextAccount(provider, currentEmail)
    if suggested != nil {
        return suggested.Email
    }

    // Fallback: first configured account
    return accounts[0].Email
}
```

## What This Does NOT Include
- Account state persistence (which account is "limited")
- Automatic account rotation
- Quota tracking per account

These are future enhancements if users want more automation.

## Success Criteria
